-- Akfen of Turkey Sells Hydro-Electric Unit to Kardemir for 10 Million Euros
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2010-12-28T05:26:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/akfen-of-turkey-sells-hydro-electric-unit-to-kardemir-for-10-million-euros.html
Akfen Holding AS, parent company of
a Turkish group active in construction, airports and ports, real
estate, tourism and energy, sold a hydropower unit to steel
maker Kardemir AS for 10 million euros ($13 million).  Akfen Hidroelektrik Santral Yatirimlari AS sold 100 percent
shares of Enbati Elektrik which will build and operate a 22.5-
megawatt hydropower plant to Kardemir, Akfen Holding said in a
statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Aydan Eksin at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net  